[[Category:Glossary]]
[[Category:OntologySync-managed-resource]]

The field of view (FOV) defines how much tissue the Miniscope can image simultaneously. It is primarily determined by the diameter of the GRIN lens and the Miniscope's optical magnification. A larger FOV captures more neurons but may reduce spatial resolution.

== Typical Values ==
* 0.5 mm GRIN lens: ~350 um FOV
* 1.0 mm GRIN lens: ~700 um FOV
* Miniscope V4 with 1.0 mm GRIN: approximately 600-700 um diameter
